&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Growth Marketing Manager on our Ecommerce Growth Team, you’ll own and optimize critical parts of the digital customer journey, driving measurable improvements in acquisition, conversion, and overall site performance. This role sits at the intersection of marketing, product, analytics, and design—focused on turning insights into action and ideas into shipped experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed, you’ll need strong analytical instincts, a bias for action, and the ability to operate autonomously in a fast-moving environment. You’ll be expected to identify opportunities, build business cases, execute experiments, and drive results—while also helping push the boundaries of how we leverage AI to move faster and smarter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor site performance and KPIs, proactively identifying funnel drop-offs, friction points, and growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own hypothesis generation, testing strategy, and execution for site experiments and personalization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute self-service updates across site content, product configuration, pricing, and experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and prioritize a roadmap of enhancements and experiments, building clear business cases and handing off well-defined work to product and engineering partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with design and analytics to develop, launch, and recap experiments, translating results into actionable insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve key areas of the ecommerce experience such as product discovery, shopping paths, checkout and other conversion flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools and capabilities to accelerate experimentation, automate workflows, and unlock new forms of personalization and self-service optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement scalable ways AI can enhance decision-making, speed of execution, and overall growth impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with product, marketing, telesales, and engineering to ensure a seamless and high-performing customer journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
