&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why are we hiring?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within our Tools and Automation organization, the Test Platform Services (TPS) team builds and operates the platforms and automation that validate SimpliSafe’s end-to-end ecosystem — spanning the full product stack: connected cameras and sensors, base stations, firmware, cloud services, monitoring workflows, and mobile applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We enable scalable, production-like validation across hardware, firmware, and distributed software systems to ensure our devices behave correctly in real-world conditions and that critical customer journeys function reliably before reaching production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Software Engineer to lead TPS’s technical vision while leading a team of engineers. This role combines hands-on architectural ownership with people leadership, execution accountability, and technical mentorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly collaborative position partnering closely with Infrastructure, Backend, Firmware, and Monitoring teams to ensure our validation platforms evolve alongside product and system complexity. It’s ideal for a leader who wants to remain deeply technical while shaping a high-impact engineering team responsible for validating complex, distributed systems at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
